- 1\nea of bubonic plague have been dis- 1\ncovered, with two deatha.\nGO UNINSTRUCTED\nNew Mexico Deiqecratlc Convention j\nDeclines McAdoo Endorsament.\n1\nBr ths Aameiatyd Pram\nRoswell. N. M., June 4. \u2014The demo-\ncratic state convention, in session\nfrom yesterday until early today,\nnamed six uninstructed delegates to\nthe democratic national convention.\nUnited States Senator Jones, the per\nmanent chairman, ruled out of order\nthe attempt to instruct the delegation\nfor McAdoo for president.\nHAVE RETURNED HOME\nAFTER ATTENDING MEETING\nJudge Carey and W. C. Deming, who\nwere here to attend the quarterly\nmeeting of the board of trustees of\nthe University of Wyoming, have re\nturned home.\nHE SAYSIT'S\nIWMBM\nGEN. WOOD DENIES CHARGES\nFRICTION AMONG HIS CAM-\nPAIGN MANAGERS\nBy the Associated Preaa. O\nChicago, June 4.\u2014Major Gene- U\nO ral Wood, today irnaqd the fol- O\nlowing: \"The report that there O\nhaa been frietltnf' asd that Colo-\nael Proctor is to cease to be my 0\ncampaign naanager. to thlae. and O\nO I can only attribute it to enemy O\nO propaganda.\u201d O\n00000000000000000\nARE MOfflK TOWARD\nDEFINITE FORMANI\nw\u2014M\u2014\n\nJOHNSONTOTAKEPERSONALCHARGEOFHBCAN\nDIDACY AND HITCHCOCK TO BE IN CONTROL\nOF WOOD FORCES ON THE FLOOR.\nA\n\u25a0y trw ABBVCIBWff PTMB.\nChicago, 111., June 4.\u2014The line* of action among the.re\npublican presidential candidates are beginning for the first\ntime to move toward definite form. The arrival of SgMMV\nJohnson to take personal charge of hi* candidacp, aaij 4hR\nagreement among the Wood leader* to have Fragit H. Hitch\ncock act a* their field marshal are the out*taa&ng develop\nment*, which indicate that within the next Forty right hrttii*\nthe situation among the republican* will move into the riage\nInhere the leaders will begin teds tart\nness. The Wood forces profess to be\nwell satlslled with the amngementa\nwithin their own ranks, and lay em\nphaaia on the statement that the hopes\nof the o